      "writtenOn": "2025-07-11T12:00:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tend to agree with Dani that a fix is needed in the global-refdb: if it is legal to create `RefUpdate`, set only the expected old value and then call `RefUpdate.delete()` then it should also work in global-refdb.\n\nAn alternative fix, also in global-refdb, may be done in the `RefUpdateSnapshot` constructor where the `newValue` passed as `null` shall be converted into `zeroId()`. I didn\u0027t test that but I believe that would be even more basic fix than the one proposed with this change.",
